editorialNotes.standard: An app parents won’t have to mute in a restaurant, this is a free-play feast with switches to flip, gears to grind, and blobs to plop together. Endlessly inventive, it’s a master class in how a simple app can sometimes feel the most advanced.

With content from big names like National Geographic, this app teaches early literacy, language, and maths, as well as social and emotional skills, throughout its more than 1,000 games, videos, and stories.
editorialNotes.short: Fun activities and lessons to instil skills in maths, phonics and more.

editorialNotes.standard: The beloved Australian pups are all here! Featuring familiar characters and settings from the show, your little ones will be frolicking with garden gnomes and hunting for hidden long dogs.

editorialNotes.tagline: Cook up a storm in the kitchen
editorialNotes.standard: Food’s fun for everyone with Toca Boca’s second go-round in the kitchen. Choose different characters and try to please their palates by preparing fish, fruit, vegetables, and more. Deciding what to serve and whether to bake, boil, fry, chop, puree, or season it—or all of the above—will keep young chefs happily cooking away.

editorialNotes.short: Read hundreds of kids’ titles that are sure to spark wonder and laughter.

editorialNotes.standard: Inspired by the popular education method based on a sensory and kinetic way of learning, this app provides a variety of activities to guide children ages 3–7 as they embark on their first steps in the world of schooling.
